  "text": "## Kafka Connect REST API Implementation Analysis\n\nAfter thorough exploration of the Apache Kafka codebase, I found that the Kafka Connect REST API implementation uses a **single unified API version** with no separate v1 and v2 implementations. The versioning that exists pertains to **connector plugins**, not the REST API endpoints themselves.\n\n### REST API Resource Handlers\n\nThe main REST API resource handlers are located in `connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/`:\n\n1. **ConnectorsResource.java** - The primary handler for all connector operations:\n   - @Path(\"/connectors\") - all connector-related endpoints\n   - Methods: listConnectors(), createConnector(), getConnector(), putConnectorConfig(), getConnectorStatus(), getTaskStatus(), restartConnector(), pauseConnector(), resumeConnector(), destroyConnector(), etc.\n   - Returns ConnectorStateInfo for status endpoints\n\n2. **ConnectorPluginsResource.java** - Handles plugin and version management:\n   - @Path(\"/connector-plugins\")\n   - Contains version routing logic via `getConnectorConfigDef()` method with @QueryParam(\"version\") parameter\n   - Uses VersionRange from org.apache.maven.artifact.versioning to handle plugin version specifications\n   - Supports version parameter format like \"latest\", \"1.0\", \"[1.0,2.0)\", etc.\n\n3. **RootResource.java** - Server info and health check endpoints\n   - @Path(\"/\") - root endpoints\n   - serverInfo() - returns kafka cluster ID\n   - healthCheck() - worker readiness check\n\n4. **InternalConnectResource.java and InternalClusterResource.java** - Internal inter-worker communication\n   - Used for cluster-internal requests\n   - putTaskConfigs(), fenceZombies(), etc.\n\n5. **LoggingResource.java** - Admin logging configuration\n\n### Task Status and Error Response Schemas\n\n1. **ConnectorStateInfo.java** - Main task status schema:\n   - Contains ConnectorState and TaskState nested classes\n   - TaskState extends AbstractState with fields: id, state, worker_id, trace, version (where version is connector plugin version)\n   - JSON format includes fields: \"id\", \"state\", \"worker_id\", \"msg\", \"version\"\n   - No separate v1/v2 implementations\n\n2. **ErrorMessage.java** - Unified error response schema:\n   - Fields: error_code (int), message (String)\n   - JSON fields: \"error_code\", \"message\"\n   - Single implementation for all API errors\n   - Generated automatically by ConnectExceptionMapper\n\n3. **Message.java** - Standard success response schema:\n   - Single field: message (String)\n   - Used for successful operations like alter offsets, reset offsets\n\n### Version Routing Logic\n\nVersion routing exists only at the **connector plugin level**, not at the API endpoint level:\n\n1. **ConnectorPluginsResource.getConnectorConfigDef()** (line 156-169):\n   ```java\n   public List<ConfigKeyInfo> getConnectorConfigDef(\n       final @PathParam(\"pluginName\") String pluginName,\n       final @QueryParam(\"version\") @DefaultValue(\"latest\") String version)\n   ```\n   - Parses version parameter using PluginUtils.connectorVersionRequirement()\n   - Creates VersionRange object\n   - Forwards to herder.connectorPluginConfig() with version requirement\n\n2. **ConnectRestServer.java** - Resource registration:\n   - regularResources() returns: RootResource, ConnectorsResource, InternalConnectResource, ConnectorPluginsResource\n   - Single set of resources registered with no version alternatives\n   - registerRestExtensions() hook for custom REST extension plugins\n\n### AbstractStatus Class\n\n**AbstractStatus.java** - Base class for status objects:\n- Fields: id, state, workerId, generation, trace, version\n- The 'version' field refers to connector/plugin version, not API version\n- Used by both TaskStatus and ConnectorStatus for consistent schema\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **No v1/v2 API separation**: The REST API uses a single unified version without separate v1 and v2 endpoint paths (no /v1/connectors or /v2/connectors)\n\n2. **No content negotiation for API versioning**: No Accept header processing or media-type versioning for different API versions\n\n3. **Version parameter for plugins only**: The only version parameter is for connector/plugin configuration definitions, not for API endpoints themselves\n\n4. **Unified schemas**: Task status (ConnectorStateInfo.TaskState) and error responses (ErrorMessage) use single implementations across the entire API\n\n5. **Internal clustering**: Inter-worker communication uses the same API handlers (InternalConnectResource extends ConnectorsResource) with internal request signatures for authentication\n\nThe Kafka Connect REST API architecture prioritizes backward compatibility through schema stability and connector plugin versioning, rather than maintaining separate API versions."
}

